        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "At least based on the description here, the current behavior is correct. In `set_completion`, `compl_autocomplete` gets cleared, so autocomplete isn’t respected in `complete()`. That’s why it always selects the first item. The docs also mention that you can use preinsert.\r\n\r\n> And is there a way to pre-select the first item, when 'autocomplete' is on?\r\n\r\nif your server support `lsp-preselect` this https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36613 should be make sense.",
